#   DIS-035: `be patch <scheme>://<host>?br` (remote-source fetch-then-merge) fails `WIREFAIL` after the bang-model landing

A `be patch` against a *remote/foreign source* ÔÇö the fetch-then-merge form `be patch ssh://origin?main` that [PATCH] ┬º"CLI use" documents ("fetches then squashes") ÔÇö fails after the DIS-030+031 bang-model landed (`bbefb693`). Both `be patch be://localhost?/beagle!` and `be patch file://$HOME/beagle?/beagle!` die `WIREFAIL` / `WIRECLFL` / `BEDOGEXIT`; the source is never fetched. Surfaced trying to merge the current trunk *into* a clone (to land GET-006/GET-004 from their be:// clones without fighting the corrupted `~/.be` copies). This blocks the loop's reconcile-in-clone path. Likely a regression in the bang-model patch shape/URI handling ([DIS-030 patch squash fork] / DIS-030+031) or the patch-side wire-fetch path. See [PATCH], [GET], [CLAUDE].

##  Issues
The host-prefixed `be patch` form no longer fetches its source.

 -  `be patch be://localhost?/beagle!` ÔåÆ `WIREFAIL` / `WIRECLFL` / `BEDOGEXIT` (the `be://` wire is also flaky/overfetches ÔÇö see [GET-005]/GET-007).
 -  `be patch file://$HOME/beagle?/beagle!` ÔåÆ SAME `WIREFAIL` ÔÇö a *local* source, so this is not just an ssh hiccup; the patch-fetch path itself is broken.
 -  Old model supported it: [PATCH] ┬º"CLI use" ÔÇö `be patch ssh://origin?main` fetches then squashes/merges.
 -  Bang-model `PATCHShape` (`sniff/PATCH.c:1314-1323`) accepts `?<br>`/`?<br>!`/`#<sha>`; the `<scheme>://<host>` prefix + the fetch handoff may be mis-parsed or dropped, or the patch-side fetch never runs.
 -  Repro context: pulling the trunk into a clone to MERGE there (the correct integrate-a-diverged-branch operation) is unreachable, so be:// clones can't be reconciled-and-landed this way.

##  Blockers
Relates to DIS-030+031 (bang model just landed) and the wire-fetch path ([GET-005] ingest, GET-007 overfetch). Needs a trace to attribute root cause (shape-parse regression vs wire client).

##  Planned
Restore remote-source `be patch` fetch-then-merge.

 -  Repro first ([CLAUDE] ┬º17): a hermetic peer (under `$HOME/tmp`, never `~/.be`); `be patch file://<peer>?/proj!` (and `?br`/`?br#`) fetches the source and weaves it ÔÇö fails today `WIREFAIL`.
 -  Trace the `WIRECLFL` origin (redirect `ABC_TRACE` to a file, grep ÔÇö never stdout): does the bang-model shape parse drop/`!`-mangle the host before the fetch, or does the patch-side wire client fail outright?
 -  Restore the fetch handoff for `<scheme>://<host>?br[!|#]` patch URIs; keep the local `?br`/`#sha` forms working.
 -  Regression test under `test/patch` (a local-exec `file://` source, hermetic).

